quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Random Numbers[/h1]

Being able to generate [b]random [/b]numbers is helpful in a number of situations, including when creating games, statistical modeling programs, and similar end products. 

In the C++ standard library, you can access a pseudo random number generator function that's called [b]rand()[/b]. When used, we are required to include the header [b]<cstdlib>[/b].[code format="cpp" codeId="239"]#include <iostream>
[b]#include <cstdlib>[/b]
using namespace std;

int main() {
  cout << [b]rand()[/b];
}[/code]
[note]This will output a random number.[/note]

